value.value: Chordotonal organ of the larval maxillary segment that possesses two scolopidia.
A multiply innervated sensillum of the larval head, located next to the labial organ whose axons project into the maxillary nerve.
Any larval sensillum (FBbt:00007240) that is part of some labial segment (FBbt:00000014).

Paired compound sense organ of the labial segment in the larval head, located on the floor of the atrium, anterior to the opening of the salivary duct (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). It is composed of 4 sensilla (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Sensory neurons travel via the labial nerve and innervate area 2 of the embryonic/larval subesophageal ganglion (Colomb et al., 2007). Neurons of the ventral pharyngeal sense organ and labial organ form a large cluster flanking the salivary duct (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

definition.value: Python and Stocker, (2002) map VPS to V1-4 in Singh and Singh (1984), but V4 seems to far posterior (posterior to DPS), so might just be V1-3.

value.value: Compound external sense organ of the late embryo or larva that is located in the lower lip of the external opening of the atrium (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997; Richter et al., 2024). It consists of 3 sensilla, one with 3 neurons and the others with one each (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997). Neurons of the labial organ and ventral pharyngeal sense organ form a large cluster flanking the salivary duct (Campos-Ortega and Hartenstein, 1997).

definition.value: Richter et al. (2024) only find the two mono-innervated sensilla on the external larva.
